8BwPwuWDS68_17RCHkf73wBKYIv8_uTtAeUxFSJyu5frk79B-q12SePhgm0U0sB5B5TFINPkPn7ZKqKmjBkEKgDaY5o\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating deserialization issues**\\n\\nI’m trying to figure out a problem with deserialization where it seems that an ObjectStreamClass constructor isn’t being reached. There might be an issue with the writeObject method not being properly invoked either. It's tricky because I need to avoid modifying any native metadata, but it seems serialization metadata might be required, which currently isn't available. It's unclear if the conditional test will generate the needed metadata since the native run lacks the necessary Object constructor. This is complicated!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining test procedures**\\n\\nI’m wondering if the dynamic report was generated during JVM testing before my test, so I shouldn’t jump to conclusions. I need to adjust the test to prevent native failures before reaching BCLMS readObject. Adding metadata isn’t an option, and there could be an error for missing serialization. However, I can't just catch unsupported tests. It seems that metadata generation should happen correctly, so perhaps tests should run under native after merging metadata. The user notes none was covered, implying that my writeObject didn’t trigger due to instrumentation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring serialization issues**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the dynamic-access call site in BCLMSPublicKey.writeObject isn't invoked by a normal ObjectOutputStream if the class isn’t recognized as serializable. The Private writeObject seems limited to serializable classes, yet BCLMSPublicKey implements PublicKey, which does extend Serializable. It looks like dynamic-access instrumentation might exclude calls if the class source file is under test. I wonder if BCLMSPrivateKey uses custom streams because the native Image version optimizes ObjectOutputStream.writeObject for byte[], so it doesn’t handle dynamic retrieval as expected.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring object reading**\\n\\nI'm reflecting on how the `readObject` method reads a `BCLMSPublicKey` object, which leads to dynamic reflection and resolves to a byte array. This helps clarify my understanding of `BCLMSPrivateKeyTest`. It seems like I need to create a similar solution for `BCLMSPublicKey`, but simply using a byte array for read and write won’t be sufficient. So I’ll need a more complex approach. This is an interesting challenge to tackle!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Native metadata for BCLMSPublicKey**\\n\\nI think I need to look into the fact that the Native might still be missing metadata for the BCLMSPublicKey object's newInstance before readObject. However, it seems that with the metadata generated from the agent, it should be fine. The dynamic coverage from JVM is seeing nested library serialization, so I should probably focus on editing this to custom streams. It's a bit technical, but let’s get it right!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JCD6sQ4KAv3qNCofsrfTcdW7|fc_05c22eae10e6d90e016a263706e43c8195b00d9b163762d7b8", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BCLMSPublicKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.pqc.crypto.lms.LMOtsParameters;", "newText": "import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.x509.SubjectPublicKeyInfo;\nimport org.bouncycastle.pqc.crypto.lms.LMOtsParameters;"}, {"oldText": "    private static byte[] serialize(BCLMSPublicKey publicKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream byteOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(byteOutputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(publicKey);\n        }\n        return byteOutputStream.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCLMSPublicKey deserialize(byte[] serialized) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectInputStream = new ObjectInputStream(\n                new ByteArrayInputStream(serialized))) {\n            return (BCLMSPublicKey)objectInputStream.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static byte[] serialize(BCLMSPublicKey publicKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream byteOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new EncodedPublicKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(\n                byteOutputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(publicKey);\n        }\n        return byteOutputStream.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCLMSPublicKey deserialize(byte[] serialized) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectInputStream = new EncodedPublicKeyResolvingObjectInputStream(\n                new ByteArrayInputStream(serialized))) {\n            return (BCLMSPublicKey)objectInputStream.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPublicKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private boolean replacedEncodedKey;\n\n        private EncodedPublicKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream)\n                throws IOException {\n            super(outputStream);\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (!replacedEncodedKey && object instanceof byte[]) {\n                replacedEncodedKey = true;\n                return new BCLMSPublicKey(SubjectPublicKeyInfo.getInstance((byte[])object));\n            }\n            return super.replaceObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPublicKeyResolvingObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private boolean resolvedNestedKey;\n\n        private EncodedPublicKeyResolvingObjectInputStream(ByteArrayInputStream inputStream)\n                throws IOException {\n            super(inputStream);\n            enableResolveObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object resolveObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (!resolvedNestedKey && object instanceof BCLMSPublicKey) {\n                resolvedNestedKey = true;\n                return ((BCLMSPublicKey)object).getEncoded();\n            }\n            return super.resolveObject(object);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2133, "output": 2161, "cacheRead": 43520, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47814, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780889311337, "responseId": "resp_05c22eae10e6d90e016a2636e011c48195b6882cecff40f1eb"}}
