castle JAR and seeing that it might not have a debug line or source, showing as \\\"Unknown Source.\\\" It looks like the JaCoCo coverage reports might not include line data but could reflect instruction instead. It's curious that all serialization tests show 0, which might be due to native test failures making the dynamic report stale. I wonder if JaCoCo is filtering out private serialization methods, but I'm not entirely sure about that.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating ObjectOutputStream**\\n\\nI'm considering the requirements for `writeObject`. It needs a `byte[]` argument, and I can't change that. If a Bouncy Castle object replaces it in a custom `ObjectOutputStream`, it might lead to issues with metadata generation. I'm wondering if the `BCLMSPublicKey` could throw an `IOException` in the process. Testing shows that the JVM passed the first run but not the second, which is puzzling. I need native passes with the replacement, but I can't seem to add generated metadata. Maybe I could catch an error during deserialization to check for `MissingReflection`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test creation**\\n\\nThe user wants tests created only under the test source root, but I see the user-code-filter is under the coord root, not src/test/java. It seems like including classes with certain patterns could cause issues with byte[] serialization. I’m wondering if changing the filter might broaden the scope to unrelated classes, which I want to avoid. \\n\\nUsing `ObjectOutputStream` or a custom `SecurityManager` also doesn't seem like the right direction, and `java.beans.XMLEncoder` doesn't fit either. It’s a bit challenging!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_VkPOeH3tZGUZ8Aot7KDcd00P|fc_05c22eae10e6d90e016a26380f6fec8195a85e0eab417a9310", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BouncyCastlePQCProviderTest.java", "limit": 120}}